{{fr-adj}}

# [[welcome]]
#: {{ux|fr|un événement '''bienvenu'''|a '''welcome''' event}}

====Usage notes====
As an adjective or noun meaning "one who is welcome," ''bienvenu'' corresponds in gender to the person who or thing that is welcome. As a noun meaning "the act of welcoming, the state of being welcomed," or an interjection meaning "Welcome!", it is always feminine: ''[[bienvenue]]''.

:{{uxi|fr|Son ami était le '''bienvenu.'''|Her friend was '''welcome.'''}}
:{{uxi|fr|Elle a souhaité la '''bienvenue''' à son ami.|She bade her friend '''welcome.'''}}
:{{uxi|fr|'''Bienvenue!'''|'''Welcome!''' (to any person or people, invariable for gender or number)}}

{{fr-noun|m|f=+}}

# a [[person]] who is [[welcome]]d
#: {{uxi|fr|Vous êtes le '''bienvenu'''|Welcome!}}
#: {{uxi|fr|Il n'est pas le '''bienvenu'''|He's not welcome.}}
